{{en-adj|-}}

# Of the same kind; [[alike]], [[similar]].
# Having the same [[composition]] throughout; of [[uniform]] make-up.
#* '''1946''', {{w|Bertrand Russell}}, ''History of Western Philosophy'', I.25:
#*: Their citizens were not of '''homogeneous''' origin, but were from all parts of Greece.
# {{context|chemistry|lang=en}} in the same [[state of matter]].
# {{context|mathematics|lang=en}} Of which the properties of a smaller set apply to the whole; [[scalable]].
#: ''The function ''f(x,y)=x<sup>2</sup>+y<sup>2</sup>'' is homogeneous of degree 2 because ''f(''α''x,''α''y)=''α''<sup>2</sup>f(x,y)''.''
